      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Essentially, as the gaps shrink toward a theoretical solid, the fabric stops being \"woven\" and starts mimicking a membrane, completely excluding most gas exchange. This transition point is where the fabric sacrifices its textile nature for that of a plastic barrier, like a sheet of dense plastic film. In pure textile terms, you hit a plateau where thread count increases yield very little measurable gain in blocking agents if the finishing chemistries aren't altered.",
